EML are computable (mainly because exp and log are computable for computable complex inputs, and the primary input ('1') is ofc computable) - this isn't as obvious as first thought, and you need some machinery from computable analysis. Ultimately, you get the canonical example of Chaitin's \\Omega_U is inexpressible in EML (it's left-c.e. but not computable).\r\n\r\nEML is also shown to be equivalent to the EL numbers due to Chow (1999). Additionally, the expressions for x*y, -x, and x^{-1} are optimal (there are no shorter EML expressions for those, by exhaustive search).","submitter_user":"unprovable","user_is_author":true,"tags":["math"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hmunw6","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hmunw6/inexpressibility_exp_minus_log"},{"short_id":"ljgmb5","created_at":"2026-05-05T00:12:47.000-05:00","title":"Using the WebView module with C++ and Qt Widgets","url":"https://www.qt.io/blog/using-the-webview-module-with-c-and-qt-widgets","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"rcalixte","user_is_author":false,"tags":["api","c++"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ljgmb5","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ljgmb5/using_webview_module_with_c_qt_widgets"},{"short_id":"kb4wwp","created_at":"2026-05-04T22:27:59.000-05:00","title":"PgQue: Two Snapshots and a Diff","url":"https://thebuild.com/blog/2026/05/03/pgque-two-snapshots-and-a-diff/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"wrs","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","performance"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kb4wwp","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kb4wwp/pgque_two_snapshots_diff"},{"short_id":"otxkjw","created_at":"2026-05-04T22:07:03.000-05:00","title":"Bun (the js runtime) is being vibe-ported from zig to rust","url":"https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/blob/claude/phase-a-port/docs/PORTING.md","score":35,"flags":0,"comment_count":29,"description":"","description_plain":